  "body": "### Description\nAs a beacon node developer, I want arithmetic over/underflow detection so that I can be fully spec-conformant. \n\nThe beacon chain specification now [explicitly states](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/beacon-chain.md#beacon-chain-state-transition-function) that `uint64` under/overflow causes state-transitions to be invalid. Our `UnsignedLong` class does not enforce this. We should enhance or replace that class to throw an exception when over/underflow occurs and make any other necessary changes.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n* Any `uint64` over or underflow in the state transition is detected and handled correctly.\n* No fuzz test or in-the-wild consensus failures due to arithmetic over or underflow.\n",
